Headlines.Author: Drew FitzGerald
Headlines.Headline: Range Resources 2Q Net Profit Soars On Higher Prices, Production

PARAGRAPH.#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Range Resources Corp.'s RRC second-quarter net profit more than quintupled as higher production volumes and climbing oil prices delivered a stronger bottom line absent the past year's charges. The better-than-expected results come after a string of losses in recent quarters caused by various charges and write-downs. Range has been selling noncore properties in recent years, using proceeds to develop areas with higher returns. The company in May sold its Barnett shale properties in Texas for about $900 million to focus on developing its Marcellus shale holdings, where fields are more productive than in some other areas and are richer in natural-gas liquids, which sell at a higher price than dry gas.

#text: By Steve Gelsi Energy stocks moved more deeply into the red than the broad market at midday Monday as crude prices fell below $50 a barrel for the first time in two weeks. With little in the way of company-specific developments, the sector took a hard look at bearishness in the overall economy, led by growing likelihood of a bankruptcy filing from U.S. auto maker General Motors Corp.
. Against this backdrop, the S&P 500 (SPX) fell 3.5% to 787, but losses in the energy patch were worse.
